{"content":"## Next Themes\nBecause you are using Next.js, you can use next-themes to implement dark mode.\n<Installation options={{ isManual: true }}  items={['next-themes']}/>\n\n## Theme Provider\nNext, you need to create a theme provider component. You can do it like this:\n```\n'use client'\n\nimport * as React from 'react'\n\nimport { ThemeProvider as NextThemesProvider, useTheme } from 'next-themes'\nimport { type ThemeProviderProps } from 'next-themes/dist/types'\n\nconst ThemeProvider = ({ children, ...props }: ThemeProviderProps) => {\n  return <NextThemesProvider {...props}>{children}</NextThemesProvider>\n}\n\nexport { ThemeProvider, useTheme }\n```\nSince you've got the theme provider in play, you'll probably wanna team it up with a route provider. Go ahead and whip up a `providers.tsx` file in your `components` folder.\n\n<PlainCode code={`'use client'\n\n  import { ThemeProvider } from 'next-themes'\n  import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation'\n  import { RouterProvider } from 'react-aria-components'\n\n  declare module 'react-aria-components' {\n    interface RouterConfig {\n      routerOptions: NonNullable<Parameters<ReturnType<typeof useRouter>['push']>[1]>\n    }\n  }\n\n  export function Providers({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n    let router = useRouter()\n\n    return (\n      <RouterProvider navigate={router.push}>\n        <ThemeProvider attribute=\"class\">{children}</ThemeProvider>\n      </RouterProvider>\n    )\n  }\n  `}/>\n\n## Usage\nAfter that, you can use it in your root layout file like so:\n\n```tsx {1} {7-9}\nimport { Providers } from '@/components/providers'\n\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }: Readonly<{ children: React.ReactNode }>) {\n  return (\n    <html lang=\"en\">\n      <body>\n        <Providers>\n          {children}\n        </Providers>\n      </body>\n    </html>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n## Theme Switcher\nFor theme switcher, you can use the `useTheme` hook from `next-themes` to get the current theme.\n\n<Installation options={{ isManual: true }}  items={['justd-icons']} />\n\n<PlainCode code={`'use client'\n\n  import { IconMoon, IconSun } from 'justd-icons'\n  import { useTheme } from 'next-themes'\n  import { Button } from 'ui'\n\n  export function ThemeSwitcher() {\n    const { resolvedTheme, setTheme } = useTheme()\n\n    return (\n      <Button\n        appearance=\"outline\"\n        size=\"square-petite\"\n        aria-label={'Switch to ' + resolvedTheme === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light' + 'mode'}\n        onPress={() => setTheme(resolvedTheme === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light')}\n      >\n        <IconSun className=\"h-[1.2rem] w-[1.2rem] rotate-0 scale-100 transition-all dark:-rotate-90 dark:scale-0\" />\n        <IconMoon className=\"absolute h-[1.2rem] w-[1.2rem] rotate-90 scale-0 transition-all dark:rotate-0 dark:scale-100\" />\n      </Button>\n    )\n  }`}/>\n\nIf you spot typos or wrong implementations, feel free to [contribute here](https://github.com/irsyadadl/d./blob/main/content/docs/dark-mode/next-js.mdx).","title":"Next.js","description":"Turning your Next.js app into a night owl? Follow this smooth guide to light up the dark mode magic.","_meta":{"filePath":"dark-mode/next-js.mdx","fileName":"next-js.mdx","directory":"dark-mode","extension":"mdx","path":"dark-mode/next-js"},"toc":[{"title":"Next Themes","url":"#next-themes","depth":2},{"title":"Theme Provider","url":"#theme-provider","depth":2},{"title":"Usage","url":"#usage","depth":2},{"title":"Theme Switcher","url":"#theme-switcher","depth":2}],"structuredData":{"contents":[{"heading":"next-themes","content":"Because you are using Next.js, you can use next-themes to implement dark mode."},{"heading":"theme-provider","content":"Next, you need to create a theme provider component. You can do it like this:"},{"heading":"theme-provider","content":"Since you've got the theme provider in play, you'll probably wanna team it up with a route provider. Go ahead and whip up a providers.tsx file